results.name: G.f. A(x) satisfies: A(x) = Product_{k>=1} (1 - x^k*A(x)^k)^k.
formula: A(x) = 1/x * series reversion of ( exp( Sum_{n >= 1} sigma_2(n)*x^n/n ) ), where sigma_2(n) = A001157(n).
Equivalently, the o.g.f. A(x) satisfies [x^n](1/A(x))^n = sigma_2(n) for n >= 1. Cf. A066398. (End)
A(x) equals (1/x) * series reversion of (x * the o.g.f. for the sequence of planar partitions A000219).  - _Peter Bala_, Feb 11 2020
maple: Gser := solve(series(x*exp(add(sigma[2](n)*x^n/n, n = 1..32)), x) = y, x):
